Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 3cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf for ~{20%minutes} - you'll roast them for longer once you've crushed them.

Meanwhile, cut the @cauliflower{1} into florets (like small trees), halving any large ones.

Pick the @mint{1%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Cut the @lemon{1} into wedges. Drain the @sweetcorn{160%grams} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the heat if necessary. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice colour.

While the sweetcorn chars, pop the cauliflower onto a baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat. Spread the florets out in a single layer.

Roast on the middle shelf until golden brown and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, combine a good squeeze of lemon juice with the @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1/2%tbsp} for the dressing.

When the potatoes have cooked for 20 mins, remove them from the oven. Use the bottom of a bowl or pan to lightly crush each potato.

> Use a #bowl{} or #pot{} to lightly crush the potatoes.

Drizzle the smashed potatoes with more @oil{}, and return to the top shelf of your oven until crispy and golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

When the cauliflower is roasted, drizzle over the @honey{1%tbsp} and toss to coat.

When everything's ready, add the cauliflower, sweetcorn, @salted peanuts{25%grams} and half the mint to the lemon dressing.

Crumble in the @Greek Style Salad Cheese{50%grams}, season with salt and pepper, then toss everything together.

Share the roasted cauli salad between your plates. Drizzle over the @soured cream{75%grams} and sprinkle with the remaining mint.

Serve the smashed potatoes alongside.

Serve with any remaining lemon wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!